thread.title: Rising Dollar Sends Gold Lower

author: Amrith Ramkumar
title: Rising Dollar Sends Gold Lower
text:
Gold prices fell for the first time in five sessions Tuesday, hurt by a rebounding dollar and placid stock moves as worries about a global trade war eased.
Gold for June delivery fell 1% to $1,347.60 a troy ounce on the Comex division of the New York Mercantile Exchange. Prices have traded between roughly $1,305 and $1,360 this year, moving within that range based on moves in the dollar, interest-rate expectations and safe-haven demand.
